Working on text material in French (literature, media, vulgarization); exercises to train the vocabulary, the pronunciation, phonetic transcription etc.  Descriptive materials to improve clear knowledge of pronunciation and text mechanisms. Analysis of text content and structure, text types, language registers and other linguistic means in their connection with the aim of the text.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Correction of the principles and practics of the pronunciation of French; training understanding and analyzing of diverse oral and written texts in FrenchLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student successfully attended the course  - has an overview of problems related to the French pronunciation and oral communication ; - is able to note different mechanisms in texts which can be used to describe the text type, lexical links, language registers, etc; - has a primary knowledge of analyzing texts' thematic and structure - has knowledge to use French language specific diacritic signs and the IPA symbols for phonetic transcription of French
